</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="135C2A627444FFEAC698F9EFFCDC988B" box="[659,783,1660,1687]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">figs 51–54</figureCitation>
), but clearly can be distinguished from it by the hind tibia black anterolaterally at least third of the length of the tibia (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627444FFEAC059F90CFB4D98A6" box="[1106,1182,1695,1722]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">fig. 48</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647444FFEAC4A5F950FE9498C0" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[174,327,1730,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Temnostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombylans">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57444FFEAC4A5F950FE9498C0" box="[174,327,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">T. bombylans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hind tibia without black mark anterolaterally, or with black mark occupying no more than one sixth of the length of the tibia, as on 
<figureCitation id="135C2A627444FFEAC737F976FC55991C" box="[828,902,1765,1792]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">fig. 52</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B167444FFEAC795F976FB17991C" author="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P." box="[926,1220,1765,1792]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 139" refId="ref7111" refString="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P. 2017. StN keys for the identification of the European species of various genera of Syrphidae 2017. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 99, 1 - 139. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin." type="journal article" year="2017">Speight &amp; Sarthou, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647444FFEAC547F89AFDCC993E" authorityName="Krivosheina" authorityYear="2002" box="[332,543,1801,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Temnostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustistriatum">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57444FFEAC547F89AFDCC993E" box="[332,543,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">T. angustistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647444FFEAC796F89AFBE6993F" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[925,1077,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Temnostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombylans">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57444FFEAC796F89AFBE6993F" box="[925,1077,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">T. bombylans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: mid tibia yellow with blackish incomplete ring (mostly expressed on the posterior side) just below the middle of tibia not less than a third of the length of the tibia (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627443FFEDC77AFF41FC689EF1" box="[881,955,210,237]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">fig. 49</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647443FFEDC7F8FF40FB5F9EF0" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1011,1164,210,236]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Temnostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombylans">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57443FFEDC7F8FF40FB5F9EF0" box="[1011,1164,210,236]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">T. bombylans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mid tibia entirely yellow, as on 
<figureCitation id="135C2A627443FFEDC5D4FF65FDF99F0C" box="[479,554,245,272]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">fig. 53</figureCitation>
), a third of the hind femur at the apex mostly with black macrotrichia (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627443FFEDC545FE8AFE499F28" box="[334,410,281,308]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">fig. 50</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647443FFEDC5DDFE89FDA39F2F" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[470,624,281,307]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Temnostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombylans">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57443FFEDC5DDFE89FDA39F2F" box="[470,624,281,307]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">T. bombylans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a third of the hind femur at the apex mostly with pale macrotrichia, as on 
<figureCitation id="135C2A627443FFEDC5CFFEAFFDDC9F4B" box="[452,527,316,343]" captionStart="Figs 47–54" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1503]" captionTargetId="figure-115@11.[174,1233,174,1503]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 47–54.Males of Temnostoma angustistriatum (figs 47–50) and T. bombylans (figs 51–54):47, 51 — habitus, dorsal view; 48, 52 — hind tibia, lateral view; 49, 53 — mid tibia, lateral view; 50, 54 — hind femur, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377562/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">fig. 54</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B913EAF57443FFEDC628FEAFFDA89F4A" bold="true" box="[547,635,316,342]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Female</emphasis>
can be distinguished by the same characters as the male except mid tibia with less expressed dark ring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
